caption: The BEST Indian food on Oahu. Some of the best Indian food I’ve ever had anywhere

First time eating at kamana and it’s a small cozy place that felt friendly and inviting.  Honestly I’ve been to many restaurants in Honolulu and this is the few times I felt happy from eating my food.     That is why I am writing this review. I will definitely go back with my family again.  The price was a little less then what you find in some of the more known spots. Nice portions.   What more can you ask for. The dress is super casual.    And the seating is pretty tight.  But that’s not really a bad thing.

Food was amazing. Service was really good complementing the food. Really good quality and authentic food. Wait time was very less. Number of people grabbing the to go orders were justified with the authenticity. 👌🏻👌🏻👌🏻 I would recommend them for anyone trying Indian food or someone used to it life long.
Wish they would put more butter on the naan.  Can't see it, taste it, or smell it.

Although food was delivered fast and hot but it was Worst Indian food Ever . Aloo paratha and paneer naan was horrible . Instead of chicken soup they delivered vegetable soup . Green chutney (sauce) was with some artificial green color and Taste horrible . Samosa was ok . Chana masala was horrible .  In short not a recommended place , avoid if possible . All 4+ star reviews seems fake .
Great food. Simple atmosphere. We really enjoyed the tikka masala, madrashi and tandoori chicken.  We plan to go back.
Definition of yummy!
A great place to spicing up your life

The ambiance and food was average. Given the little options we have in Hawaii for Indian food, if you are craving for Indian food, you can give it a try. We ordered Chicken Tikka Masala and it was undercooked. We told them it was undercooked, they did replace it for us but by the time we received the curry, our bread and rice were cold. So we did not enjoy our food.
Small restaurant that packs a big punch. The food was delicious & the service was very friendly. Chicken Tandoori was the best I've had. Good size portions, too. Highly recommend.

Got the chicken marsala and some garlic naan. I have to say it was delicious! They asked if I wanted spicy and I regret my decision I underestimated the spice ! It was still delicious. Highly recommend
Delicious food and awesome people!
Tandoori chicken and garlic naans are to die for
Everything was delicious!Super yummy and great service!
Still a go to spot for me , Chicken Tikka Masala, and Chicken Vindalu is my favorites.  Garlic naan is a must!! Service is always friendly and fast.
Veggie Samosas  and the lamb curry lunch with mango chutney. Very fresh and delicious best ive tasted in a long time.
Hands down the best Indian food in Hawaii!!

It has been our biweekly curry take out place.  There are few good Indian restaurants we like in Honolulu but ever since we tried Kamana kitchen, we are hooked.  Everything we tried so far over the past few months are great.  We like Tandoori meat items and Naan, Roti and other Naan. They are delicious. Vegetarian menu are as good.  They know how to blend the spice.  When you order curies, they give you very generous portion of basmati rice.  We save them to make fried rice later.  Haha  All are take out.  Very happy to find this place.
This is my favorite place to eat. Their curries are so rich and tasty. The portions are generous they are super fast too.

Holy wow. 3 months of traveling to Mumbai, Kolkata, and Goa made me crave Indian food. Good indian food. This was one of my complaints about Hawaii, it was hard to find authentic Indian Food. Not anymore.  Kamana Kitchen not only does thalis, but they are HUGE!  Definitely worth the price. Can't wait till I'm craving indian food again. So ono!  धन्यवाद Mahalo!

This place is actually giving you the experience of dine in. I couldn't poop for 2 days straight after I landed in maui and I was worried. I went there, they served curry in papar plates and bowl, not even a regular size plate but a smaller one(dessert plate) and you won't believe I had diarrhea. It cleaned my stomach. I feel much better now. Thank you for the amazing diarrhea inducing dinner.
Kamana Kitchen serves the best Indian food in downtown Honolulu.

Pretty good Indian food. I love malai kofta and theirs is descent. They also have paratha which I like. This is my favorite Indian food on oahu. I am pretty sure I've eaten at all of them as of end of 2020.
Tasty food and good food portion.
Delicious Indian food served here. The lunch plates are a fantastic deal and if you love eggplant like I do, be sure to get it.

Edit to add photos: just went back today. The food is even BETTER than I remember it. I love that there is always an Indian family eating dinner when we come in. I’ve tried most of the other Indian restaurants on the island, and this one is HANDS. DOWN. THE BEST!  By far my favorite Indian restaurant in Hawaii. I’ll drive to Chinatown from Kapolei for this food. I’ll find street parking on a busy night. I’ll drag my keto husband along and make him break his diet, all for that amazing sweet and savory almond-and-raisin stuffed peshwari naan. God damned delicious.  The pekora, the curries, and the tandoori meats are all delicious too. I’ve tried most of them. But definitely get the Peshwari naan. Even now, my mouth is watering.

Good Indian food. Nice size portions as I usually have enough for lunch the next day. The chicken tikka masala can be a bit tough sometimes but, the sauce is delicious. The naan is always good and warm. I've never dined in here. It's usually pretty warm in the restaurant when I take out so, I probably won't. Service is quick but, the woman working out front seems to be on her own and overworked while the owners sit by. Nice place overall.
Excellent Indian cuisine
Ordered vegetarian - received chicken.  Customer service wasn’t helpful. Never again, absolutely unacceptable. Reported to the health department
Really like that they have a variety of vegan options. The aloo gobi is my personal fave! One of the few places open late in downtown.

We ordered Lunch Chicken Tika masara and Lunch Lamb Tika masara. Soooo delicious. I was in India for a year n I was looking for truly delicious Indian restaurant in Oahu. I know some of places they always have a lot of customers but I do recommend here. I can say that here is the best Indian food in Oahu!
Best Indian food I ever have and I had a lot. Tasty and delicious.

One of the best Indian restaurants we’ve been to! This was our first dine-in dinner since the Oahu stay at home order was in place and am I glad we came to Kamana Kitchen! We ordered the lamb masala, chicken biryani, and the non-vegetarian thali plate. They were all so good! We couldn’t decide on naan so we ordered the garlic and peshwari naan. Delicious! Highly recommend both! We will definitely be back!
Amazing food! And they have lunch specials from 11 to 3.
Sooo good. So many flavors. Some of the best I've had in a while.
Amazing food!!!! Highly recommend!!
Good food. decently priced.
Great hole in the wall indian spot! Food and service 5 out of 5
Love the lamb saag at Kamana Kitchen. They do not skimp on the lamb and the curry is creamy and packed with mild spice flavors. Perfect over basmati rice and cheesy garlic naan bread!

Ordered this through bite squad, food came quicker than they text which was awesome.  Everything was still nice and hot, but cool enough to eat right away.  We are new to Indian food, so we can't quite comment on the particular flavors, but everything that we ordered tasted really good, we got the fish coconut curry, lamb curry, chicken saag, and chicken makhani, along with regular, garlic, cheese naan, and roti.  Overall everything was awesome.  The fish curry was the favorite of the four, the chicken makhani was good without a starch, the lamb curry was a tiny bit spicy but only after the initial bite, and the chicken Saag was great with the naan.  It was a fun eating experience, because we were able to dip the naan like they do on TV, that was probably the best thing about the whole experience.  The only issue was that there were a lot of large spice pieces left over. They either need to blend the spices better or strain them out. Too many spit out pieces...  Would definitely order again sometime.

Lady that took our order was so friendly and helpful with food recommendations.  The order was ready in about 5 minutes and was excellent.  Got the order to go but will think about dining in next time.
Gold

ONLY place I'll go for truly authentic Indian food!!!! Everything is always delicious and fresh whether you eat there or get it to go. They give you big portions which some other places won't but charge the same amount. The staff is very friendly and accommodating, especially to first timers. It took me 8 years to get my boyfriend to try indian food and the staff was so patient and answered all of his questions. Now he loves it and won't go anywhere else. MUST TRY is their Tikka Masala!!!!! Favorite at any spice level!!!!
Highly recommended
Me and my husband went here for lunch and had their lunch special, the price it great and the food was delicious and full of flavors. Will definitely come back.
The biriyani was good and it was more than beef for one person I wish to order normal spicey
Ordered the carryout tikki masala lunch special spicy and it was fantastic. I've tried lots of Indian food places and this is one of the best. Highly recommend!

I'm thoroughly pleased with my experience at Kamana Kitchen. It's a quaint little hole in the wall serving up those traditional and savory Indian dishes we all love. The location was simple enough to find (no parking, so you can either Uber or take the #1 or #2 bus and get off on Hotel St & Bishop). Adequate, but "intimate" seating. The lack of space is made up with the service and the food. I had the channa masala (ordered it medium spicy because I love some heat) and an order of garlic naan. I was a little sad they did not have the traditional chutneys for dipping my naan, but the flavor of the masala more than made up for that. Rice is included with your entree! The prices are reasonable (average for Indian food) and the portion sizes are substantial. I ate a lot in the restaurant and still had leftovers. Definitely worth coming again.
Food was hot and very flavorful. My husband and I love Indian food and this place did not disappoint.  Will be going again real soon.
Cant believe it took me so long to find this place! Awesome food and extremely friendly and welcoming staff!
Food is amazing but parking is a hassle
Solid Indian food for lunch.  Hard to find in Hawaii.
Long wait but tasty food
Very friendly staff and good food
Decent lunch specials at reasonable prices. Good portions.

My wife and I have been to India. We practically lived there for over 2 months. Hands down,  Kamana Kitchen is the best Authentic Indian food you can get on Oahu. Kamana Kitchen maid us feel like we were back in Goa at Anjuna beach eating at one of their many Indian restaurants. Place is way cleaner and healthier than any restaurant in India. The price is worth every penny. Staff is actually from India. Generous portions. And most of all I can’t wait to back and eat there again. This will definitely be one of our go to places for Authentic Indian food.
Ordered take out to try. Instead of Chicken, we received the wrong dish, which had no chicken and was insanely spicy. Food was bland, rice cold, and cheesy naan had no cheese at all. Avoid
Great lunch menu and specials. Staff is really friendly and nice.
Worst service ! Very poor quality food and definitely would not recommend this place for vegetarians !!

Not a good customer service representative and he is very harsh even to take orders. Also they give just one spoon of raitha for biriyani and if we ask for extra they will charge 4$. Strictly would not recommend to my friends.!!
It's a tiny place with great tasting food

Christmas Day and Kamana is just one of the only places open around in Honolulu. I was told by the host that it would take at least an hour to get a table! I looked for other nearby places and none of them were open 😐  We decided to wait and are so glad that we did so. The food at the end of one hour wait was absolute fab and we just loved it.  Both paneer and dal were sumptuous and we were extremely pleased with the restaurant and the service.
Best Indian food in Oahu

We went to Hilo and Kona if the same restaurant and loved it there  Service was much better there He said no plastic cups for kids i could see it right there and he gave it to other kids  W came at 3 but by the time he took order it was 3.05 so refused to give the lunch menu which was still ok but the over all service was very ordinary and so was alacarte food too  Here the people serving  were rude and not very friendly
The food is not special at all. For the price, the food quality is nothing. Nothing taste to what an indian restaurant would taste.

Food was good.We ordered chicken biryani and chicken tikka masala,both were delicious.Just few drawbacks - Due to heavy rush the service was a bit slow and also the restaurant is a bit tacky,not too spacious n fancy.But worth a try if you crave for Indian food in Ohau
Good food..great service...the people were very good....
Tasty food in downtown Honolulu; always a pleasure visiting a restaurant run by Nepalis

I've enjoyed Indian cuisine for decades halfway across the state's and Kamana Kitchen is one of the best places I've ever had the luxury to enjoy. Never had Indian food and don't know what to get? Not a problem. Try their royal platters. Either the vegitarian or meat. Both are an excellent deal and absolutely delicious. They also offer vegan options.

I go here every week before a regular rehearsal down the street. The food is great, with options for every diet including a whole vegan section of the menu if you're into that. I almost always get the vegetarian thali because it's a huge amount of food for $20. Veggie samosa, veggie pakoras, naan, rice, 3 entree portions (option to substitute what you prefer), chutney, and rice pudding. Usually I take some home for lunch the next day! Can't recommend this enough if you like Indian food.
I can finally say I've had amazing Indian food in Hawaii.
1st time there,  food was.delicious
The food is really good at a very reasonable price. 9.99$ lunch is worth every penny.
Food is excellent. As requested it was warm and spicy. Delivered on time. Service was also great. Highly recommended for Indians missing good Insian food while on holiday in Honolulu

They are not at all vegetarian and customer  friendly. We ordered combo of veg and paneer pakora and told twice to the person who took order that we are vegetarians. Since we went to kamana kitchen at 8:30pm we had to do to- go. Then when we came back to hotel and opened pakora, it was chicken and veg mix pakora and also we ordered butter roti he gave just regular roti which was very hard to eat. I recommend vegetarians not  to go to kamana kitchen in Hilo, big island. I have been in Honolulu that’s good.
Authentic Indian food at a very reasonable price. Friendly and efficient staff.
The best and only authentic Indian restaurant on Oahu. Their lunch plate is awesome for the price and dinner also very good. If you want to try real Indian food please visit this place.
If you are around for lunch, it's a good buy. The location, specifically the parking hassle is the biggest detractor from more frequent visits.

0 star  I ordered 2 aloo paratha - it was horrible. Aloo was nowhere to be seen. I trashed half untouched, and almost 1 out of remaining 1.5 after scavenging for aloo. It tastes just roti - thick roti.  To make it worse - I asked for little achaar with paratha. They asked 5$ for it. That was outrageous. Nearly all places have achaar, chutney as a complimentary side . Even if you ask for price, it should be reasonable. Price of achaar more than price of paratha - never seen anywhere else. If your food tastes good - noone should need achaar in first place.  After a long tiring day at Maui, I had to sleep hungry. I did not have energy to find another place and this was terrible. I hate to throw food but had no other option.

Excellent food!

Awesome 👍 Food.

Always love coming here.  Great lunch specials

The absolute best Malai Kofta I have ever had in my life. Everything was delicious. Service was excellent. Our server was very friendly, always smiling and checking on us, and took the time to explain our menu choices to us. This is my new favorite place to eat in Honolulu.

I walked out and looked through my to-go bag and felt something was off aside from me missing my utensils.  I said eh, it's only utensils.  Then I realized I did not get my mango lassi!  I think I was two blocks away. I walked back and the lady who took my order was tending to a table so I waited a bit. She didn't even flinch to look who came in the door. Mind you, the place was not busy.
Came here with 2 friends, all three of us loved our dishes.
Best malai kofta on island. I will go back many times because of this dish. It is my favorite! Thank you for having it.

I've had Kamana Indian Cuisine on my mind since March 2018 but have finally gotten around to trying them.  What brought us here to try them was our visit to the recent Honolulu Magazine's Best Of... Festival and their award-winning Biryani rice.  We wandered into this restaurant around 11:30am when it wasn't quite yet crowded with other downtown workers.  Since there were only the two of us, we were directed to sit at a table for two either along the front window or along the wall away from the entrance.  What struck us immediately was the very warm temperature in the restaurant which we figured to be because the outside temperature was so hot and our humidity just sat on our chests like an elephant.  But, there was an air-conditioner that was doing its best to cool down the space.  As we were walking to our table, our server followed us while bringing menus and glasses of iced water.  She was friendly and asked if we've eaten Indian food before or if we needed suggestions.  We did peruse both the regular menu and the lunch specials even though we already had in mind what we planned on ordering.  FOOD: -Biryani with chicken:  traditional aromatic Basmati rice tossed with herbs and spices with chunks of tender chicken.  The portion was huge, as my husband and I paired it with the lunch special, we had left overs.  Indeed, this Biryani rice was flavorful and reminded us of what we've eaten at Singapore's Tiffin Room (Raffles) and Little India neighborhood or Los Angeles' Badmaash Restaurant.   We agreed with Honolulu Magazine's voters for awarding this dish as a winner.  $15.95  -Saag Paneer (Lunch Special):  served on a Thali (compartmental metal tray), generous portions of saag paneer, yellow dal, vegetable curry of the day, achar (Indian pickles), half naan and basmati rice were steaming hot and appetizingly aromatic.  It was a good call to order this lunch special to pair it with the biryani as we got to sample more dishes than to have just ordered an additional entrée of saag or curry or mixed grill.  After all, it was lunch time and we didn't want to overeat and fall into food coma.  $9.99  Food flavors, portions and value are excellent here.  Service was friendly though a bit spotty as the restaurant filled but still good.  There seemed to be more people ordering and picking up their takeout than dining in.  Perhaps they had already experienced the warmer room temperature of the restaurant.

I do not typically take pics of my food but I had to capture the moment -- hense the partially eaten plate. This. Is. Really. Seriously. Tasty. The chicken tikka was spot on. The rice was fluffy & light spiced. The naan wasnt as "pillowy" thick &fresh but I doubt they have an oven onsite, so thats understandable.  And if you ask for spicy, they will gve you spicy! Be careful what you wish for. But hands down the  best Indian food ive had in years, second only to the UK (I haven't been to India yet).  I'm going to miss you .
We have had very tasty Indian vegetarian food here. We liked it.

Go to order is the chicken tikka masala medium spice! This dish was bursting with aromatic flavors and just the perfect amount of heat and spice. Paired nicely with the slightly sweet naan and long grain saffron rice. I definitely was in heaven and super sad it was gone. And you bet I used that naan to scrape up every bit of that yummy sauce.
Good food
We loved the food and the spicy level are very well managed
Bistro style. Good food.

I finally got around to visiting this place and was pretty disappointed: had the lunch special (lamb), it just didn't have fantastic flavor. It's as if it was intended for people who don't really care about flavor or people who are in a rush to get back to work. Google suggested this place and compared it to Himalayan kitchen. Good taste of food. Good service, clean, can take away available, malai kofta and chicken tikka recommended. Can try gajar ka halwa and some indo-nepalese sweets.
Very nice food, tasty and felt light after eating. Parking around that place can be a bit tricky

omg amazing food
Authentic north indian food! Delicious!

A surprisingly good Indian restaurant operating out of Honolulu. We are visiting from Dallas and this place will give most of the Indian restaurants a run for their money. We came here for dinner last night and ordered yellow dal fry, kadhai paneer and the chicken tikka. Very flavorful, not overly hot and just perfectly spiced. The onion kulcha was very fluffy and had a unique heat to it which tasted great. Definitely recommend people to stop by.
The food was good. Even my north Indian mom was happy with the food.
Horrible food..

The place is small and if you don't go there at the right time it's jammed packed. The food is delicious. It's served hot and visually appealing. The aroma has you salivating and ready to dig in. I caution you to take your time and appreciate all the flavors that come with the curry or masala. Do not be in a rush to gulp down the tika or cheese naan. Talking of the naan it is fluffy, thick, and chewy. It's a minefield of tastebuds pleasure. Like any other establishment there are quirks to the place. The selection is smaller than other places I've been to, service is slow but the waiter is nice, and the structural/visual layout is dissapointing at best. Try and go at times when it's slower for better service. Prices are fair.
Excellent place for a quick lunch sets! Recommend it alot! Also open in evening for dinner also!

The food here is absolutely delicious.  It is reasonably priced and it is clean.  The only downside to this restraint is the la know convenient parking.  That being said there are a few local parking lots that are minutes away and are OK priced.
We have ordered Vegetable biryani,chicken curry and butter naan. The taste is average. Complete North Indian style food. Disappointed ☹️..
Delish authentic food. Good service. Lunch is a good deal
Delicious! The naan is fantastic, as is the palak paneer.  They also give generous portions.

I ate here a few weeks ago and the chicken in my tikka masala was incredibly overcooked. I was excited to try this place because the one in Hilo is consistantly amazing but it let me down. The sauce was good but still I was disappointed by the chicken. I might give it a second chance though, because that was the only downside.

The mushroom matar was very delicious, maybe even better than the Maui branch! We also had the saag paneer which was good. Great quantities in both the dishes. If you are craving for Indian food in Oahu, this is probably the best place to visit!

I've been to nearly every Indian restaurant in my 4 years of living on Oahu. This is by far the best. Bombay Palace and Maharani are okay, Bombay Palace is service oriented, food is bland. Maharani is not service oriented and food is exquisite. Kamana is right in the middle with prompt service, and great tasting Indian food. Chicken Tikka was out of this world!
I live in Maui and by far the best Indian cuisine! The Lamb Kadhai really well cooked. Delicious.
Veggie biriyani was very tasty, a little oily though. The vegetarian thali was also good. Overall good meal.
Everything was delicious, the spice level was a little higher than I expected, but still very edible (we ordered medium and that was perfect).  I would recommend this place to my friends.
when i miss indian food, i eat here. biryani is decent. ask for mild one. spicy is too hot. Even for an Indian its way too hot.

Food is very tasty. Best place for Indian food in downtown. This is the only place in Oahu for best Biryani (don't compare with main land taste). Curry and sauce texture and color is too good and tasty. Samosa is good. Don't try gulab jamun. Thali available here.

I swear by the saag paneer here. The first time I tasted it I had tears lol Now, I am by no means an expert on saag paneer or Indian food but there was something special about it. I always get medium heat, but I love spicy food so last time I got spicy. Glad I tried it but I’ll probably stick to medium next time. :)

From the Hilo location: First time trying Indian food. I love the mango lassi, had the non-vegetarian Thali royal platter and was enough to share with a friend. I tasted and enjoyed everything on the platter. Ask for the mild if you're not into too much heat. Definitely recommend trying this place. Will visit again.

We walked in expecting a meal, we did not expect a true dining experience. From the instant we opened the door, we were greeted by the enticing sights and sounds of Bollywood and the gentle wafting of fresh naan from the kitchen.  Upon sitting down, the first things that greeted our eyes were a delicate paper placemat and paper napkin to match. Not to worry, we were soon served a green cloth napkin upon a porcelain plate. It was a good thing that my dining partner and I had both wore green to complement the napkin. Next we received the gold-embellished menu, which was adorned with appetizing photos of the options. We were glad to see many options for vegetarians, vegans, and meat-eaters alike. We ordered samosas first. They were brought out on a silver platter with two delectable dipping choices. Our main courses arrived with a side of butter-brushed naan glistening. Our waiter had outstanding spacial awareness and an artistic eye for where to place the food for maximum dining experience. The food was excellent, but it was after we had finished eating that the true service began. Our waiter surrepitiously peaked his head around the corner to assess our progress. He did not rush us, like many restaurants you find in America. Finally, after I had concluded my post-meal nibbling, he brought us a thoughtfully arranged array of boxes designed to hold every type of leftover we possessed. He even, like a magician, produced a plastic bag designed to hold our one, treasured leftover piece of naan. As we stood to leave, I accidentally forgot my bag in the establishment. But I did not fret! When I stepped back in to retrieve it, he was already prepared to chase me down the steeet to return it to me. Overall, this was a delightful and delicious experience.

We discovered this places as we were walking around downtown trying to find someplace that was open on new year's. I ordered the malai kofka and my husband ordered the non-vegetarian plate. Everyone was delicious and we loved being able to try so many things on his dish.
My 2 nd visit food is good even if you like hot order mild slow inattentive wait staff
No customers, just one coom6

I have not seen the kind of service so far in any restaurant. Is it the lack of Indian restaurants on the island that’s making them behave this way? We were three and were given a table for two when there were vacant tables available. When we asked him to at least add another table next to the one given to us, we were told to leave. The restaurant was awfully small and dirty anyway. So, we felt that it was better to not eat in such a place because we never know the quality of their kitchen either!
Awesome Indian food. Best Indian food in Honolulu.

Visited this restaurant for lunch. This restaurant is like a chain and has branches in other hawaii islands. I visited the one in maui and was very impressed. Came here with similar expectations but was disappointed. The restaurant is near the lolani palace and is very small. The food itself was pretty good and spicy. However, as others have mentioned, the waiter acted like a weirdo. He wouldnt respect anybody, would do the exact opposite of what you would want. For example , to save time i went to the counter to hand my card. He asked me to go back to our table. Took his sweet time to pick up the cheque, but wouldnt come back to the table. Gave it to my mom who was leaving the restaurant and asked her to hand it over to me. Based on the reviews, i am not alone in my opinions about this guy. The other person who served the food was very polite.
Good fresh food and good service!
The dal fry is excellent. The naan is good too.

Staff was friendly by answering our questions and even telling us a bit about the preparation of the food (example it takes them 5 hours to make their rice pudding which is tasty!)  Service was quick and food was delicious. You can tell that it's prepared with care.  My husband had the Non-Vegetarian Thali -medium heat (sampler platter) and I had Chicken Saag-mild heat. The staff does ask how hot/spicy you want your food. Please remember this is Indian spiciness not that mild American spicy, so medium is good for people that like hot stuff.  Portion sizes are generous so it's worth the money.  Can't wait to go back!
Good location. Got the chicken tikka masala which was tasty but there was some licorice flavor in there that I didn’t care for. Would go back to try a different dish.

Food quality is okay at best. Definitely not worth the price tag. Waiter was pushy, rude, and when I asked for a to-go container for my unfinished food the busboy took it away and apparently trashed it. When I asked the waiter what happened to my food he said "you should have asked for a to-go container." It's one thing to make a mistake and apologize for it. But to tell me, to my face, I'm the one who made the mistake in a situation you didn't even see is unacceptable. Kamana Kitchen will not be receiving any more business from me.

Served stale chapatis. I ordered Paneer tikka masala which had very few pieces of cottage cheese and Chicken tikka masala was not at all actual tikka masala but tasted as butter chicken.  Stale chapatis gave us restless night. Definately not recommended.

Very accommodating service, friendly staff, and amazing food with reasonable prices.

I've ordered twice from this restaurant and the first batch of curry was very greasy. Unfortunately, the grease overpowered the taste of the curry. After refrigerating it and then reheating it enough to decant the oil into the sink, the curry was indeed tasty! I ordered a second time and well... it was again very greasy. The price is right at this restaurant, I wish they held back a little on the oil. I cannot recommend them at this time.

The service here is great but the Indian food here is ok. I had the chicken vindaloo but it just tasted like lemon chicken. The citrus was way too overpowering and the spices were not that strong. In addition, their spiciness levels were not that spicy, even at the hottest level.

Slightly pricey at around $15 per entree, but plenty of food to go around.  Their butter chicken and tiki masala was very tender, however not as flavorful as I had imagined.  Their lamb curry was quite good however.  Garlic naan was great as well as their mango lassi.  Don’t be afraid to go spicy as it is not that spicy.
The best food the best priced, the most amazing Indian food ever!  get your butt over there and you will enjoy every bit of lunch or dinners

Hands down best Indian restaurant I’ve been on Oahu so far. Their potato stuffed naan is addictive and highly recommended. Their portions are good and prices are reasonable. I’ve been trying to find a go-to Indian place and I think this is it. The atmosphere is really nice and laid back.  Less crowded than other places we’ve been to. Weekends street parking is allowed so we just parked on the street. I ordered the malai kofta, which was delicious! I’d say that you can taste the difference between mine and my husband’s dish. He ordered a lamb dish but I forget the exact name. We’ll definitely be back!
